headlines.description: — All-Star starter Trae Young had 22 points and six assists and the Atlanta Hawks routed the Orlando Magic 130-109 on Wednesday night in the final game before the break for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young scores 22 points, Hawks rout Magic 130-109

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant hit the winning basket and scored 24 points to help the Detroit Pistons end an eight-game losing streak and the Boston Celtics' nine-game winning streak, 112-111 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons end 8-game skid, Celtics' 9-game winning streak

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton leaned on Tristan Thompson for advice when the two were traded to Indiana last week.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers snap 7-game losing streak by beating Wizards 113-108

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The Brooklyn Nets aren't sure when Kevin Durant can come back or how soon Kyrie Irving might be able to play in New York.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas leads Nets back from 28 down to stun Knicks 111-106

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan's spectacular run is now one for the NBA record book.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan breaks Wilt's record as Bulls beat Kings 125-118

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Jusuf Nurkic had 32 points and eight rebounds, Anfernee Simons added 31 points and six assists and the Portland Trail Blazers overcame Ja Morant’s 44-point performance, beating the Memphis Grizzlies 123-119 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blazers overcome Morant's 44 points, beat Grizzlies 123-119

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Keldon Johnson scored 22 points, and the San Antonio Spurs defeated the Oklahoma City Thunder 114-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Keldon Johnson scores 22 as Spurs top Thunder 114-106

headlines.description: — Even without Chris Paul, the Phoenix Suns did what they've done pretty much every time they've taken the court this year.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns rally without Paul, edging Rockets for 7th straight win

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — The Golden State Warriors wanted to go into the All-Star break on a winning note after a tough stretch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morris returns from concussion to send Nuggets past Warriors

events.name: Utah Jazz at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James was at the Super Bowl Sunday when he saw Aaron Donald and the Los Angeles Rams rally in the fourth quarter to win a championship.
headlines.shortLinkText: James fuels Lakers' 4th-quarter rally over Jazz, 106-101
